newsitem.title: UK: NWE jet fuel premiums unchanged in slow discussion.
newsitem.headline: NWE jet fuel premiums unchanged in slow discussion.

text.p: NWE jet fuel premiums drifted sideways in desultory business on Tuesday, traders said.
Discussion was overshadowed by a lack of vessels at economic rates and modest to poor physical demand.
Benchmark front month February IPE gas oil futures closed down $5.25 at $203.75 a tonne, dragged lower by weaker NYMEX heating oil, ample supply and warmer European weather.
Cargoes were stable at Feb IPE +$33/34 cif NWE. NWE barges were Feb +$30/31 fob ARA, unchanged. Traders reported scattered buying interest into Scandinavia.
